# Readen landing page (lp)

## Filipi (collaboration)

Filipi Rafaeli is building Readen (readen.co). He's the product owner and sole developer.
He thinks in product terms, gives blunt design feedback, and previews changes in the browser himself.
Prefer concise, technical responses; execute end-to-end.

---

## Purpose

The marketing site for the Readen app — "the reading app you close". It sells the app's calm, craft, and curation, and must itself meet the app's polish bar. The app repo at `../readen` is the source of truth for concept, palette, and any UI being showcased (widgets, session, shelves, goals).

---

## Tech stack

- Next.js (App Router, `src/app/[locale]/…`) — version is ahead of training data; check `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before using unfamiliar APIs
- Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first config in `src/app/globals.css` via `@theme inline`)
- next-intl — locales **en / pt / es**, messages in `src/messages/*.json`, routing in `src/i18n/`
- MDX blog — content in `src/content/blog/{locale}/*.mdx`, helpers in `src/lib/mdx.ts`
- bun as package manager and script runner
- Deployed page routes: home, `/about`, `/blog(+slug)`, `/privacy`, `/terms`

---

## Structure

- `src/components/brand/` — the identity primitives: `Logo`, `Cover`, `Shelf`, `PhoneFrame`, `EditorialHeader`
- `src/components/marketing/` — one file per homepage section, composed in `src/app/[locale]/page.tsx`
- `src/components/ui/` — small reusables (`Reveal`, `Button`, `StoreBadge`, `NumberTicker`, `SessionTimer`, `StarRating`, `Accordion`, `Marquee`, …)
- `src/lib/config.ts` — store links, contact email, catalog stats; `src/lib/data/` — shelf books, people, mock books; `src/lib/constants/` — per-component layout constants
- `src/lib/seo.ts` — `buildMetadata` + JSON-LD builders; every page defines `generateMetadata`

---

## Hard rules

- **Every user-facing string** goes through next-intl and exists in all three of `en.json`, `pt.json`, `es.json` (same keys, `en` is the reference).
- **Responsive is non-negotiable** — every section verified at mobile (375), tablet, and desktop, in light and dark.
- Book covers come from `SHELF_BOOKS` (Open Library) via the `Cover` component; remote image hosts are allow-listed in `next.config.ts`.
- Homepage sections Filipi considers done (keep, don't redesign without being asked): the three feature demos (scan/sessions/goals), Discover ("curate"), Reviews, Onboarding ("build your shelf"), FAQ, footer.
- Verify with `bun run lint && bun run format:check && bun run typecheck && bun run build` before calling work done — CI runs exactly these.
